03/30/2017
truefoodsinc







            🌶Yummy idea for lunch or dinner. 🥕🍃🍅Repost from @rachels.healthy.home_ww - Look at those colors 😍 I had a…                            read more&gt

🌶Yummy idea for lunch or dinner. 🥕🍃🍅Repost from @rachels.healthy.home_ww - Look at those colors 😍 I had a humongo bowl of my Thai Chicken Zoodles for dinner. So good and super filling! Recipe below ⬇7sp
.
.
Sautée red and/or yellow bell pepper (~1/4-1/2 of a pepper) in 2 tsp toasted sesame oil (2). Once peppers started to soften add 1 medium spiralized zucchini and season everything with salt, pepper, a little sriracha, and garlic powder. Once the zucchini is 90% cooked add 3 oz cooked shredded chicken (2) and almond butter sauce (3). When the zucchini is finished cooking and the chicken is warmed through, top everything with cilantro (optional but recommend!) and green onions. The almond butter sauce is: 1 tbsp almond butter mixed with 1 tsp coconut aminos (can sub low sodium soy sauce), ~1/2 tsp ginger paste (found in a tube in the produce section), ~1/2 tsp sriracha, and 2 tsp water, mixed well. NOTES: Tonight I threw in some purple cabbage because I had it on hand. Sometimes I add shredded carrots or regular onion as well. Just add any extra ingredients like that when the peppers are sautéing. Frozen peppers and onions work just fine.👌 Don't be afraid to play around! .
.
#weightwatchers  #healthyrecipes #cleaneating  #smartpoints #wwsmartpoints #wholefoods #buzzfeedhealth #buzzfeedcleaneating #thekitchn #nytfood #foodgawker #huffposttaste #buzzfeast #eatclean #eatingwell #feedfeed #f52grams #heresmyfood #tastingtable #foodandwine #zoodles #almondbutter #lowcarb  #foodisfuel  #realfood  #eeeeeats #jerf #whole30approved #paleo #sriracha















 




