12/09/2016
truefoodsinc







            Meatloaf a winter favorite ❄️☃️ 🍴🍅 Do you know the ((healthy turkey meatloaf)) muffin man...errrr lady💁🏻?!…                            read more&gt

Meatloaf a winter favorite ❄️☃️ 🍴🍅 Do you know the ((healthy turkey meatloaf)) muffin man...errrr lady💁🏻?! .
Get some MUCH NEEDED extra #veggies this time of year with my Healthy Turkey Meatloaf Muffins thanks to @truefoodsinc BBQ sauce ((yup, the BBQ sauce has veggies!!)) and riced cauliflower! 🍅🍠 Taste-tester approved, #glutenfree, made with only 8 REAL ingredients (plus spices) + adorably cute because everything tastes better when it’s mini and made in a muffin tin! ✔️
.
📍Here’s how to make it >> In a large bowl, combine the following ingredients + mix to combine: 1 lb organic ground turkey, 1/2 c. chopped onion, 1/2 c. riced cauliflower, 2 grated garlic cloves, 1/4 c. + 2 tbsps quick oats, 1/4 c. ground flaxseed meal (or an additional 1/4 c. oats), 1 large egg, 1/4 c. + 1 tbsp @truefoodsinc BBQ sauce, 1/4 tsp each black pepper, salt + smoked paprika and 1 tsp no salt Italian seasoning.
Spray your muffin tin with nonstick spray + divide the batter evenly among 10 muffin cups (about a heaping 1/4 cup of the meatloaf mixture in each). Spread 1 tsp @truefoodsinc BBQ Sauce on top of each meatloaf muffin. 
Bake for 15 minutes @ 350F, then remove from the oven, add another 1/2 tsp @truefoodsinc BBQ Sauce on top of each meatloaf muffin and bake for another 5 minutes. The turkey meatloaf muffins will be slightly browned at the edges when done cooking with edges slightly removed from the tin. Serve immediately or allow to cool completely before freezing. 💯🍴
Full recipe on www.CitNutritionally.com!
